#
# safemoded.rc — init service descriptor for SafeModeService.
#
# This file is installed to /vendor/etc/init/safemoded.rc by the build system
# (via init_rc in Android.bp). Android's init process reads all *.rc files in
# /vendor/etc/init/ at boot time.
#
# ── How init starts this service ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# "class main" means the service belongs to the "main" service class.
# init starts all "main" class services automatically when the system reaches
# the "class_start main" trigger in the global init.rc (which happens during
# normal boot). No manual "start" command needed in init.rc for class=main.
#
# ── user system / group system ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The service runs as the "system" UID (uid 1000).
# This is the standard UID for platform services that need to:
#   - Register with ServiceManager
#   - Communicate with VHAL (via Binder IPC)
# Running as "root" is intentionally avoided — principle of least privilege.
#
# ── No chown/chmod needed (unlike ThermalControl) ────────────────────────────
# SafeModeService reads VHAL via Binder IPC — it does NOT access sysfs directly.
# Therefore no filesystem permission setup is needed in this RC file.
# (Contrast with thermalcontrold.rc which needs chown on hwmon sysfs files.)
#

service safemoded /vendor/bin/safemoded
    class main
    user system
    group system
